          0,
          [],
          0,
          "That’s right: Sweden, Denmark, and more than 30 other countries offer many residents so-called “return-free filing,” whereby the government does the tax preparation itself. Though the systems vary, the basic process is this: Tax authorities use employers’ filings to calculate levies that are owed, then send taxpayers their forms already filled out and let them decide whether to sign and pay or do the calculations on their own."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
